    "He was appointed full professor in 1950, succeeding <a href=\"/warnerl\">Langdon Warner</a> in responsibility for the Asian collections of the Fogg Museum.": [],
    "In 1953 his published the <em>Pelican History of Art</em> volume on India.": [],
    "The following year, he wrote a modest textbook for a cross-cultural course at Harvard, <em>Art in East and West</em>.": [],
    "The little book, like his Pelican volume, became a basic introduction for students of west art to the sensibilities of Asian esthetics and arts.": [
